    "### 2.5 Out-of-Sample Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "The selected breakout parameter is evaluated in the out-of-sample period to test whether the signal remains plausible outside the parameter search period.\n",
    "\n",
    "A breakout signal is usually more selective than a simple momentum signal because it only invests when the stock reaches a new high relative to the previous trading range. Therefore, the strategy may spend long periods in cash. This can reduce downside risk, but it can also cause the strategy to miss parts of a recovery if the price does not reach a new high quickly enough.\n",
    "\n",
    "The out-of-sample validation helps assess whether the selected breakout window provides a reasonable balance between signal frequency and signal quality."
   ]
