    "### 2.6 Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "The plots compare the out-of-sample portfolio value of the trading-range breakout strategy with a buy-and-hold benchmark. The breakout strategy only invests after the stock breaks above a recent high. Therefore, the strategy can remain in cash for extended periods when no new breakout occurs.\n",
