    "## Section 3: Signal 3 — Volatility-Adjusted Momentum\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.1 Economic Motivation and Literature\n",
    "\n",
    "The third signal is a volatility-adjusted momentum signal. It is based on the idea that positive momentum is more meaningful when it is large relative to recent risk. A stock may show a positive past return, but if this return occurred during a highly volatile period, the signal may be less reliable.\n",
    "\n",
    "This signal therefore combines the trend-following idea of time-series momentum with a risk adjustment. Instead of only checking whether past return is positive, the strategy evaluates whether the past return is large enough relative to recent volatility.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.2 Signal Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "The momentum component is defined as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "M_{t,n} = \\frac{P_t}{P_{t-n}} - 1\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Recent volatility is estimated as the rolling standard deviation of daily returns over \\(m\\) trading days:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sigma_{t,m} = \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{m} \\sum_{i=0}^{m-1}(r_{t-i} - \\bar{r}_{t,m})^2}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The volatility-adjusted score is then defined as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Score_t = \\frac{M_{t,n}}{\\sigma_{t,m}\\sqrt{n}}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The trading signal is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Signal_t =\n",
    "\\begin{cases}\n",
    "1, & \\text{if } Score_t > c \\\\\n",
    "0, & \\text{otherwise}\n",
    "\\end{cases}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where \\(n\\) is the momentum window, \\(m\\) is the volatility window and \\(c\\) is the score threshold.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.3 Parameter Search\n",
    "\n",
    "This signal has three parameters: the momentum window, the volatility window and the score threshold. The parameter search tests combinations that represent different momentum horizons, different volatility estimation periods and different levels of signal strictness.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Parameter | Meaning | Values Tested |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `momentum_window` | Number of trading days used to calculate momentum | 60, 120, 180 |\n",
    "| `volatility_window` | Number of trading days used to estimate recent volatility | 20, 60 |\n",
    "| `score_threshold` | Minimum volatility-adjusted momentum score required for investment | 0.25, 0.50, 0.75 |"
   ]
  },
