   "source": [
    "### 3.4 In-Sample Results\n",
    "\n",
    "The table above reports the in-sample performance of the volatility-adjusted momentum signal for different parameter combinations and stocks. The results are ranked by Sharpe ratio and total return.\n",
    "\n",
    "Compared with the simple time-series momentum signal, this signal is more selective because it requires the momentum score to be strong relative to recent volatility. The score threshold controls how strict the signal is: a lower threshold creates more trading signals, while a higher threshold requires stronger risk-adjusted momentum.\n",
    "\n",
    "The parameter search helps evaluate whether the volatility adjustment improves the signal quality or whether it makes the strategy too restrictive. A suitable parameter combination should produce reasonable risk-adjusted performance and should be economically interpretable."
   ]
